modules.description: Provides functions to manage event loops using an underlying event library, including initializing the system, setting up events with file descriptors and callbacks, and controlling the execution of the loop. Operates with event structures, file descriptors, and custom event flags. Used to handle asynchronous I/O operations and event-driven programming in network applications.

Handles event-driven I/O operations using libevent, including adding, removing, and managing event callbacks. Works with event structures, file descriptors, and timeout values to monitor and respond to I/O and timer events. Used to implement non-blocking network servers and asynchronous task scheduling.

Manages event loops with low-level event handling, enabling asynchronous I/O and event-driven workflows through event structures, file descriptors, and custom flags. Supports initializing the event system, registering events with callbacks, and controlling loop execution. Operations include adding, modifying, and deleting events, as well as managing their states. Example tasks include monitoring socket activity, scheduling timed events, and responding to system signals.
